{{also|Frei|-frei|freí}} ==German==
===Etymology=== From {{etyl|goh|de}} {{term|frī|lang=goh}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|de}} {{m|gem-pro|*frijaz}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|de}} {{m|ine-pro|*prei-||to be fond of}}, {{m|ine-pro|*prey-}}. Compare Dutch {{term|vrij|lang=nl}}, English {{term|free|lang=en}}, Danish {{term|fri|lang=da}}.
===Pronunciation=== * {{IPA|lang=de|[fʁaɪ̯]}} * {{audio|De-frei.ogg|Audio}} * {{rhymes|aɪ̯|lang=de}}
===Adjective=== {{de-adj|freier|freisten|sup2=freiesten}}
# [[free]] # [[released]], [[unimprisoned]], [[unenslaved]] #: ''[[w:Stadtluft macht frei|Stadtluft macht '''frei''']].'' #:: ''City air makes one '''free'''.'' (German [[serfs]] who escaped to and lived in cities for a certain period of time were legally freed.) # [[unblocked]] # [[liberal]] # [[free of charge]], [[gratis]] {{qualifier|see usage notes}} # [[unlimited]], [[unconstrained]] # [[licentious]], [[unrestrained]]
====Usage notes==== ''Frei'' can mean “free of charge” only in the context of public services, e.g. ''freie Krankenversorgung'' ("free medical care"), and in some fixed expressions such as {{term|Freibier||free beer|lang=de}} or {{term|freie Kost und Logis||free board and lodge|lang=de}}. Otherwise, ''frei'' is not applicable in this sense.
====Synonyms==== * (''unbound''): [[ungebunden]] * (''unconstrained''): [[ungezwungen]] * (''liberal''): [[liberal#German|liberal]], [[freiheitlich]] * (''free of charge''): [[kostenlos]]
