# {{context|sometimes with ''[[littera]]''|lang=la}} {{Latn-def|la|letter|1}}

==={{abbreviation-old|la}}===
{{head|la|abbreviation}}

# {{context|in dates|lang=la}} ''[[ante]]'' (“before”)
#: '''''A.''' D.'' — ''ante diem''
# {{context|in dates|lang=la}} ''[[anno]]'', ''[[annus]]'' (“year”)
#: '''''A.''' U. C.'' — ''anno urbis conditae''
#: '''''A.''' P. R. C.'' — ''anno post Romam conditam''
# [[Aulus]] (a Roman given name)
#* Inscriptiones Orelli 1530: '''''A'''. '''A.''''' — ''Auli duo''
# [[aquae]] (“waters”)
#* Inscriptiones Orelli 1643 sequens; 2620; 3011: '''''A.A.''''' — ''Aquae Aponi'' (“[[w:Abano Terme|Abano Terme]]”)
# ''[[auro]]'', ''[[argento]]'', or ''[[aeri]]'' (the three directors of the mint)
#* Inscriptiones Orelli 569; 2242; 2379; 3134 alia: ''III. VIRI '''A.''' '''A'''. '''A.''' F. F.'' — ''auro, argento, aeri flando, feriundo''
# [[agris]] (“fields”)
#* '''''A.''' D. '''A.''' — ''agris dandis adsignandis''
#* '''''A.''' I. '''A.''' — ''agris judicandis adsignandis''
# {{context|upon the voting tablets in judicial trials|lang=la}} [[absolvo]] (“I free”, “I acquit”)
# {{context|in the Roman Comitia|lang=la}} [[antiquo]] — “I leave in its former state”, “I reject” [e.g. the point in question]
# [[amicus|amicō]] (“friend”)
#: '''''A.''' O.'' — ''amico optimo'' — “best friend”
# ''[[a]]'' (“to”)
#: '''''A.''' P.'' — ''a populo''
# aediliciae
#: '''''A.''' P.'' — ''aediliciae potestatis''
# [[aerario]]
#: '''''A.''' P. R.'' — ''aerario populi Romani''
# {{context|in Cicero's ''Tusculanae Disputationes'', “Tusculan Disputations”|lang=la}} ''[[adulescens]]'' or ''[[auditor]]'', one of the disputants, as opposed to ''M.'' for ''[[magister]]'' or ''[[Marcus]]''

